Defendant Ashley M. Stone in court.  Chad A. Hendee appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Atty hendee states that the defendant sent the court a letter for early termination of probation.    Court advises defendant of right to an attorney.  Defendant wants to proceed without.    Court finds waiver of attorney made freely, voluntarily & Intelligently.
Court questions the defendant regarding her letter.  
Atty Hendee makes arguments.

BY THE COURT:  Court denies the defendant's request for early termination of Probation.
to Court from DOC Agent Evers
Probation review hearing on November 3, 2017 at 01:30 pm.
to Court from Ashley M Stone

Defendant Ashley M. Stone in court with attorney Mark Jay Gumz.  Chad A. Hendee appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
  Atty Hendee states plea agreement.  Defendant to enter plea and there is a joint recommendation for probation with conditions.  Atty Gumz agrees.  Defendant enters No Contest plea.  Court questions defendant regarding plea. Advises of Constitutional Rights and elements of the charge.  Court finds plea made knowingly, voluntarily & Intelligently.  Court relies on the criminal complaint for a factual basis.  Court questions Atty Gumz.  BY THE COURT:  Court finds a sufficient factual basis to support the charges.  Court accepts defendant's plea and finds defendant guilty.
Counsel make sentencing arguments.  Defendant makes statement.

BY THE COURT:  Sentence withheld, defendant placed on probation for a period of 36 months.  Conditions:  *Pay costs of $268.00.  *Counseling as recommended by the agent.

  **Court advises defendant that they have been convicted of a Felony and advises rights of voting privileges and of owning a firearm.

Defendant Ashley M Stone in court with attorney Mark Jay Gumz.  Chad A. Hendee appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
  Atty Hendee states that in speaking with Atty Gumz; the defendant will be waiving the Prelim today.  Atty Gumz agrees and has discussed the waiver with his client.   Court questions the defendant.  Defendant agrees with the waiver.  Court accepts the waiver of the Prelim.

  BY THE COURT:  Court finds probable cause that a felony was committed and this defendant committed it.  Case bound over for trial or further proceedings.

Court gives 30 days for the information to be filed.
Atty Gumz enters a Not Guilty plea.
BY THE COURT:  Not Guilty plea entered.
Set for Return.
bond continued.

Defendant Ashley M Stone in court with attorney Mark Jay Gumz.  Chad A. Hendee appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
